.TH "drm_atomic_helper_page_flip" 9 "drm_atomic_helper_page_flip" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_atomic_helper_page_flip \- execute a legacy page flip
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_atomic_helper_page_flip
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ","
.BI "struct drm_framebuffer *fb "  ","
.BI "struct drm_pending_vblank_event *event "  ","
.BI "uint32_t flags "  ","
.BI "struct drm_modeset_acquire_ctx *ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
DRM CRTC
.IP "fb" 12
DRM framebuffer
.IP "event" 12
optional DRM event to signal upon completion
.IP "flags" 12
flip flags for non-vblank sync'ed updates
.IP "ctx" 12
lock acquisition context
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Provides a default \fIdrm_crtc_funcs.page_flip\fP implementation
using the atomic driver interface.

See also:
\fBdrm_atomic_helper_page_flip_target\fP
.SH "RETURN"
Returns 0 on success, negative errno numbers on failure.
